{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Line a fine-mesh sieve with a nut milk bag and place over a bowl.  Place bowl with sieve onto mixing bowl lid and weigh yoghurt into it. Add orange blossom water and place into refrigerator until mixture thickens (approx. 3 hours).","Place yeast, sugar and water into mixing bowl and heat <nobr>3 min\/37°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add semolina, flour, cream of tartar, salt and milk and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Set mixture aside to prove in mixing bowl for 1 hour.","Add bicarbonate of soda and mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Leave mixture to prove in mixing bowl for a further 5 minutes or until it starts to bubble.","Place a non-stick frying pan over medium heat and add butter. Grease 4 egg rings with butter and place into frying pan for 1 minute to warm. Sprinkle some semolina into each ring. Fill each ring three-quarters full with batter. Keep heat at medium and cook for 5 minutes or until surface is dry to the touch. Carefully remove rings with tongs, then flip beghrir over and cook for a further 3 minutes (adjust heat as needed to ensure cooking is slow and even). Transfer into a thermal serving bowl or onto a plate and cover to keep warm. Add more butter to pan, re-grease rings as needed and repeat process for remaining batter (makes approx. 10 beghrir). Serve with Orange blossom yoghurt and marmalade."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["500 g natural yoghurt","1 - 2 tbsp orange blossom water","1 tsp dried instant yeast","½ tsp sugar","300 g water","130 g fine semolina, plus extra for sprinkling","200 g plain flour","¼ tsp cream of tartar","1 tsp salt","200 g milk","1 ½ tsp bicarbonate of soda","butter, for frying","orange marmalade, to serve"]}],"id":"r431908","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-S_-EBielZ2c\/XZWZ9nMu6dI\/AAAAAAAAeUI\/fIAi7sMSiwUgY8kGAUrwmCsYFkuk_RhowCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_rCf4Bvv7U43K5jk9.png","title":"Orange grove beghrir with orange blossom yoghurt","publishedAt":"2019-04-